author: Corridor Crew
description:
Making Superman's flight believable for the big screen was quite a challenge back in 1978. Directed by Richard Donner and starring Christopher Reeve, Superman: The Movie was the most expensive film made at the time, with a budget of $55 million. Without the existence of CGI, they developed new optical tricks to create the illusion of flying.

Do you think they pulled it off?
title: You Will Believe a Man can Fly
